<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 12 at 7:16AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
Areas of dense fog have developed across the area due to light
winds and low level moisture. As steadier rains move in and winds
pick up the next few hours, the fog will dissipate from west to
east.
Motorists driving should exercise extra caution and be prepared
for rapid changes in visibility. Use low beam headlights and allow
for extra spacing between vehicles.</description>
